- Release 2.0 (blue sky)

- Think about ports to wxWindows, Python, ...

- Release 1.0 (the destination)

- Get it all right
- Integration with e.g. tv card software 
	- developed and maintained by a leutenant (i.e. not me)
	- Needs ability to start/stop viewing and recording
	- Might use JNI?
- Internationalisation
- Printing
	- Keep the browser option for maximum compatibility
	- Add save html option
	- Support tv_to_latex tool, viewing and printing (what about windows?)
	- How to print on Windows?
	- Use Java's printing capabilities?
- Use JNI for grabber etc?
- FAQ?
- Other platforms - investigate Mac, BSD, others
- Consider a C++ installer that just checks for the right java version before
  running the Java installer.
- Automated bug reporting e.g. when the grabber fails.
- Automate upgrading XMLTV without upgrading FreeGuide?
- rpm/deb/proper Linux installer
- Integration with PIMs (http://www.imc.org/pdi/) and cron to alert when
	programmes are going to start
  
- Release 0.7 (nice features)

- Alert me when my programme starts
- Do some profiling and algorithm thinking and get startup time down if poss.
- Fix feature that if you reinstall to a new dir the old install can't be
	uninstalled (well, you have to delete the directory instead...)
- Help manual
- Properties box for a programme showing longer descriptions, other DTD stuff
- Further visual enhancements and customisability
- Other installer features? e.g. 
- single channel view
- Facilitating the download of listings outside of FreeGuide
	(e.g. via a cron job, or at ppp connect)
- Error message on RegExp error in Favourite editor
	
